3. RATIONALE FOR DUAL LICENSING
The dual license reflects a core principle of Algorapolis: governance architecture must be freely implementable (hence MIT for code and technical specs) while the intellectual and philosophical framework must remain open, attributed, and shared under the same terms (hence CC BY-SA for content).

This means:
- You can implement Algorapolis technical specifications in code without licensing restrictions (MIT).
- You can build commercial products based on the technical architecture (MIT).
- You must attribute the original framework when using, sharing, or adapting the written content and research (CC BY-SA).
- Derivative works of the written content must use the same CC BY-SA license — knowledge built on Algorapolis must remain as free as Algorapolis itself (CC BY-SA's share-alike provision).

This is consistent with the framework's principle that governance tools must be accessible to all civilizations while the intellectual foundation remains a shared commons.

